### TechnightApi Spring Boot - HTTP Test File
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or IntelliJ HTTP Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

### Get All Examples
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/examples

### Get Example by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/1

### Get Non-Existent Example (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/999

### Create New Example
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/examples
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test Example",
  "title": "Test Title",
  "description": "This is a test example created via HTTP client",
  "isActive": true
}

### Create New Example (without optional fields)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/examples
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Minimal Example",
  "title": "Minimal Title"
}

### Create Invalid Example (missing required fields - should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/examples
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "description": "This will fail because name and title are required"
}

### Update Example (ID 1)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Updated Example Name",
  "title": "Updated Title",
  "description": "This example has been updated",
  "isActive": false
}

### Partial Update Example (ID 2) - Only update name
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/2
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Partially Updated Example"
}

### Update Non-Existent Example (should return 404)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/999
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "This will fail"
}

### Search Examples by Name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/search?name=First

### Search Examples (empty query - should return all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/search

### Search Examples (no match)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/search?name=NonExistent

### Delete Example (ID 2)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/2

### Delete Non-Existent Example (should return 404)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/examples/999

### OpenAPI Specification (JSON)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/openapi

### Swagger UI (HTML page)
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger

